{{Infobox journal | title = Medical Law International | cover = Medical Law International.jpg | abbreviation = Med. Law Int. | editor = S. Harmon, P. Case | discipline = [[Medical law]] | publisher = [[SAGE Publications]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1993-present | openaccess = | license = | website = http://mli.sagepub.com | link1 = http://mli.sagepub.com/content/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://mli.sagepub.com/content/by/year | link2-name = Online archive | ISSN = 0968-5332 | eISSN = 2047-9441 | CODEN = MLINFN | LCCN = sn94038297 | OCLC = 30062912 }} '''''Medical Law International''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[law review]] that covers issues in [[medical law]], [[bioethics]], and health governance. It was established in 1993 and is currently published by [[SAGE Publications]]. The [[editors-in-chief]] are Shawn Harmon ([[Edinburgh Law School]]) and Paula Case ([[Liverpool Law School]]). The journal was established by Dianne Longley and Vivienne Harpwood and was edited by Shaun Pattinson from 2005 to 2011.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Building on success |author1=Shawn Harmon |author2=Paul Case |year=2011 |journal=Medical Law International |volume=11|pages=259–261}}</ref>
